{"id": "ifleet-IF-109", "issue_number": 109, "issue_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/issues/109", "pr_number": 112, "pr_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/112", "repo": "weautomatehq1/IFleet", "title": "feat(observability): route haiku-gate-passed through structured event sink", "body": "## From T5 overnight cleanup\n\n`src/pipeline/runner.ts:173` currently logs `reviewer:haiku-gate-passed task=\u2026 round=\u2026 gate=\u2026` via `console.warn`. That keeps lint happy (the no-console rule allows `warn`/`error`) but it is semantically an observability event, not a warning, and it does not flow through the event log that other reviewer-step events use.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Emit a structured `reviewer.haiku_gate_passed` event via the existing observability layer (whatever pipeline events use today).\n- Remove the `console.warn` from `runner.ts`.\n- Tests assert on the event log, not on the console spy.\n\nfrom:T5", "diff_url": "https://patch-diff.githubusercontent.com/raw/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/112.diff", "merged_at": "2026-05-19T10:06:12Z", "reviewer_login": "monstersebas1", "files_changed": ["src/pipeline/__tests__/runner.test.ts", "src/pipeline/runner.ts", "src/pipeline/types.ts"], "loc_added": 48, "loc_removed": 10, "merge_sha": "d1c7460e1ce8e9bb12de78c1ba4949aded0774c9", "in_eval_set": true}
{"id": "ifleet-IF-107", "issue_number": 107, "issue_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/issues/107", "pr_number": 110, "pr_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/110", "repo": "weautomatehq1/IFleet", "title": "fix(mcp,classifier): wire MCP submitSprint to classifier SprintMode via label", "body": "## From T5 overnight review\n\nThe MCP `submitSprint` tool (`src/mcp/tools/submit-sprint.ts:75-79`) writes the mode into the issue body as:\n\n```\n<!-- source: mcp -->\n<!-- mode: overnight -->\n\n<brief>\n```\n\nT4's done note describes this as the \"documented contract\" for the classifier to pick up. **But the classifier does not read it.** `detectExplicitMode` in `src/classifier/modes.ts:92` uses regex `/^\\s*mode\\s*:\\s*([a-z]+)\\s*$/im` \u2014 that does not match `<!-- mode: foo -->` because of the `<!--` prefix.\n\n## Options\n\n1. Update the classifier regex to also match HTML-commented directives: `/^\\s*(?:<!--\\s*)?mode\\s*:\\s*([a-z]+)\\s*(?:-->)?\\s*$/im`.\n2. Update MCP `renderBody()` to emit a plain `mode: foo` line instead of an HTML comment.\n3. Or: emit a GitHub label (`mode:foo`) when MCP submits the issue \u2014 the classifier already detects `mode:*` labels (`detectExplicitMode` lines 83\u201390).\n\nOption (3) is cleanest because labels are first-class GitHub citizens (filterable, visible in the UI) and the classifier already prefers them. Recommend.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- A sprint submitted via `submitSprint({ mode: 'ralph', ... })` produces a routing decision with `mode === 'ralph'`.\n- Tests cover all three signal sources (MCP body, plain `mode:` header, `mode:*` label).\n- Pairs with the followup that swaps the literal enum (link the two issues).\n\nfrom:T5", "diff_url": "https://patch-diff.githubusercontent.com/raw/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/110.diff", "merged_at": "2026-05-19T09:54:12Z", "reviewer_login": "monstersebas1", "files_changed": ["src/classifier/__tests__/mcp-integration.test.ts", "src/mcp/__tests__/submit-sprint.test.ts", "src/mcp/tools/submit-sprint.ts"], "loc_added": 74, "loc_removed": 12, "merge_sha": "4b16737a3f5209b8f617e579f5b73ecbcf1b43c3", "in_eval_set": true}
{"id": "ifleet-IF-106", "issue_number": 106, "issue_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/issues/106", "pr_number": 110, "pr_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/110", "repo": "weautomatehq1/IFleet", "title": "fix(mcp,classifier): wire MCP submitSprint to classifier SprintMode via label", "body": "## From T5 overnight review\n\n`src/mcp/tools/submit-sprint.ts:13` currently uses:\n\n```ts\nmode: z.enum(['normal', 'overnight']).optional()\n```\n\nThese were the values of the OLD `SprintMode` union before T3's PR #104 renamed it to `SprintOperatingMode` and made the new `SprintMode` the classifier per-task modes (`standard | ralph | ulw | tdd | deslop`).\n\nT4's own done report flagged this: *\"swap the local z.enum(['normal','overnight']) literal in src/mcp/tools/submit-sprint.ts for the real SprintMode import once T3 has landed.\"*\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- The MCP `submitSprint` `mode` field uses the classifier `SprintMode` values, NOT the operating-mode values.\n- The body header emitted in `renderBody()` is in a form the classifier's `detectExplicitMode` will actually parse (see followup #B below \u2014 currently the HTML comment `<!-- mode: x -->` is NOT picked up by the regex `/^\\s*mode\\s*:\\s*([a-z]+)\\s*$/im`).\n- MCP tests updated.\n- Typecheck + lint + test pass.\n\nfrom:T5", "diff_url": "https://patch-diff.githubusercontent.com/raw/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/110.diff", "merged_at": "2026-05-19T09:54:12Z", "reviewer_login": "monstersebas1", "files_changed": ["src/classifier/__tests__/mcp-integration.test.ts", "src/mcp/__tests__/submit-sprint.test.ts", "src/mcp/tools/submit-sprint.ts"], "loc_added": 74, "loc_removed": 12, "merge_sha": "4b16737a3f5209b8f617e579f5b73ecbcf1b43c3", "in_eval_set": false}
{"id": "ifleet-IF-098", "issue_number": 98, "issue_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/issues/98", "pr_number": 105, "pr_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/105", "repo": "weautomatehq1/IFleet", "title": "chore: brief library + dead-code audit + post-merge lint cleanup", "body": "## Context\n\nIssues #75 and #76 are stuck with `auto:failed` labels from the crash loop fixed in PR #97. The queue now correctly skips `auto:failed` issues (terminal state), so they won't be retried automatically.\n\n## Why NOT yet\n\nThe root cause of the original failure is **undiagnosed**: the pipeline editor returned `ok=true` with an empty diff. This is a silent failure \u2014 the worker subprocess's stdio was set to `'ignore'` (PR #95), leaving no logs. Stripping `auto:failed` before fixing the underlying bug means #75 and #76 will re-run, hit the same silent failure, and re-acquire the label.\n\n## Unblock order\n\n1. PR #97 merged \u2705 \u2014 crash loop broken\n2. Worker stdio routing shipped (follow-up to PR #97) \u2014 `worker-${issueNumber}.log` now captures output\n3. Trigger a new sprint on any issue to produce a log \u2192 inspect `.omc/logs/worker-<n>.log` \u2192 diagnose the editor-produces-no-diff root cause\n4. Fix the editor bug\n5. **Then** strip `auto:failed` from #75 and #76 so the fleet retries them\n\n## How to strip the labels (when ready)\n\n```bash\ngh issue edit 75 --remove-label \"auto:failed\" --repo weautomatehq1/IFleet\ngh issue edit 76 --remove-label \"auto:failed\" --repo weautomatehq1/IFleet\n```\n\n## Labels\n`auto:failed` issues: #75, #76", "diff_url": "https://patch-diff.githubusercontent.com/raw/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/105.diff", "merged_at": "2026-05-19T09:48:21Z", "reviewer_login": "monstersebas1", "files_changed": [".omc/STATUS.md", "docs/T5-audit.md", "docs/briefs/.gitkeep", "docs/briefs/README.md", "docs/briefs/chore-remove-stale-tx-todos.md", "docs/briefs/docs-adapter-self-registration-comment.md", "docs/briefs/feat-classifier-brief-to-routing.md", "docs/briefs/feat-sprint-completed-duration.md", "docs/briefs/feat-wire-classifier-into-smoke.md", "docs/briefs/fix-derive-branch-name.md", "docs/briefs/fix-empty-queue-error-message.md", "docs/briefs/fix-open-pipeline-pr-ready.md", "docs/briefs/fix-reviewer-not-weaker-than-architect.md", "docs/briefs/fix-sentry-undefined-flush.md", "docs/briefs/test-complexity-low-defeats-rule-promotion.md", "src/discord/client.ts", "src/discord/index.ts", "src/orchestrator/index.ts", "src/pipeline/__tests__/runner.test.ts", "src/pipeline/runner.ts"], "loc_added": 434, "loc_removed": 12, "merge_sha": "fa4038d56158c555c856118ce21bc8bca73f0331", "in_eval_set": true}
{"id": "ifleet-IF-076", "issue_number": 76, "issue_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/issues/76", "pr_number": 101, "pr_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/101", "repo": "weautomatehq1/IFleet", "title": "feat(pipeline): doctor extension \u2014 fingerprints, Haiku scan, daily rollup", "body": "## Behavior\n\nThe doctor gains three new cadences beyond its current on-demand CI-fix role:\n\n1. **Real-time fingerprint match** \u2014 before any LLM call, the CI log is matched against a table of known failure signatures. A match immediately applies a recovery strategy (escalate model, retry clean, double timeout) without spending tokens.\n\n2. **Periodic Haiku scan (15 min)** \u2014 a background `DoctorScheduler` reads recent failure events and asks Haiku to identify emerging patterns. Uses its own dedicated single-worker Haiku pool so scans cannot starve active tasks.\n\n3. **Daily rollup (midnight)** \u2014 aggregates the day's failure patterns and appends a dated section to `<repo>/.ifleet/learnings.md` so the auto-router (#75) can load them on the next sprint.\n\nFive new recovery strategies:\n- Architect fails twice \u2192 escalate to opus\n- Reviewer rejects twice for the same reason \u2192 bump model + flip provider\n- Verify timeout \u2192 double the timeout and retry once\n- Worktree allocation conflict \u2192 prune and retry\n- Doctor cap hit \u2192 post Discord message (\u2705 = skip, \u274c = fail, 30-min silence = fail)\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] A CI log containing `\"Cannot find module\"` or `\"TS2307\"` matches the `tsc-no-module` fingerprint\n- [ ] Fingerprint match is applied before any Haiku/runDoctor call (verified via attempt count in tests)\n- [ ] Two architect failures escalate the architect spec to opus and retry; already-at-opus \u2192 fail with `'architect failed at max tier'`\n- [ ] Reviewer concerns repeated across two rounds (first 40 chars overlap) trigger model escalation + provider flip\n- [ ] A verify timeout doubles once; a second timeout fails the task normally\n- [ ] Doctor cap hit **with** `DISCORD_IFLEET_WEBHOOK` configured: posts Discord message with \u2705 / \u274c instructions, polls for reaction, 30-min timeout auto-fails\n- [ ] Doctor cap hit **without** Discord URL: preserves current fail-immediately behavior\n- [ ] `DoctorScheduler.runScan()` fires every 15 min, emits `doctor.scan_report` event, writes `.omc/sprints/doctor-scan-latest.json`\n- [ ] Daily rollup fires at midnight (wall clock), appends `## YYYY-MM-DD` section to `.ifleet/learnings.md` without overwriting existing content\n- [ ] Rollup creates `.ifleet/learnings.md` if it does not exist\n- [ ] All strategies have per-task retry caps \u2014 no infinite loops possible\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n**New files:**\n\n| File | Purpose | ~Lines |\n|---|---|---|\n| `src/pipeline/fingerprints.ts` | Schema, 5 built-in fingerprints, `matchFingerprint()` | +80 |\n| `src/pipeline/recovery-strategies.ts` | Strategies 1/2/3/5/7 implementations | +120 |\n| `src/pipeline/doctor-scheduler.ts` | `DoctorScheduler` class \u2014 scan + rollup | +150 |\n| `src/pipeline/__tests__/fingerprints.test.ts` | Fingerprint match tests | +40 |\n| `src/pipeline/__tests__/recovery.test.ts` | Strategy unit tests | +80 |\n| `src/pipeline/__tests__/doctor-scheduler.test.ts` | Scan + rollup tests (mock workerPool) | +60 |\n\n**Modified files:**\n\n| File | Change | ~Lines |\n|---|---|---|\n| `src/pipeline/runner.ts` | Fingerprint check before doctor, strategy hooks, cap-hit handler | +60 |\n| `src/pipeline/types.ts` | Add `verifyTimeoutMs?`, `verifyDoubled?` to `PipelineInput` | +5 |\n| `src/orchestrator/index.ts` | Instantiate `DoctorScheduler`, pass `eventLog`, wire Discord URL and dedicated scanner pool | +30 |\n\nTotal: ~625 lines net new.\n\n**Built-in fingerprints (v1 seed):**\n\n| id | patterns | strategy |\n|---|---|---|\n| `tsc-no-module` | `\"Cannot find module\"`, `\"TS2307\"` | `escalate_model` |\n| `esm-require` | `\"ERR_REQUIRE_ESM\"`, `\"Cannot use import statement\"` | `escalate_model` |\n| `lint-fail` | `\"ESLint\"`, `\"lint failed\"` | `escalate_model` |\n| `test-timeout` | `\"Timeout\"`, `\"exceeded\"`, `\"jest --testTimeout\"` | `double_timeout` |\n| `worktree-conflict` | `\"worktree already exists\"`, `\"already locked\"` | `retry_clean` |\n\n**Scanner pool (Q5):** Dedicated single-worker Haiku pool wired via `OrchestratorOptions.scannerWorkerPool?: WorkerPool`. Omitting it disables the scheduler cleanly.\n\n**Rollup timing (Q4):** `DoctorScheduler` calculates ms until next 00:00 local time on start, schedules first rollup with `setTimeout`, repeats with `setInterval` every 24 h.\n\n**Doctor cap Discord gate (Q3):** Polls Discord message for `\u2705`/`+1`/`rocket`/`hooray` (skip) or `\u274c` (fail). 30-min no-reaction \u2192 auto-fail.\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Worktree prune implementation (belongs in `PipelineRunnerFactory`, separate issue)\n- Extending fingerprint table beyond v1 seed set\n- Strategy 2 `allowProviderFlip` field (can be revisited if cross-provider rule conflicts)\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Soft dependency on #69 (3a \u2014 learnings.md path) for rollup destination\n- Soft dependency on #75 (4a \u2014 auto-router) to consume what rollup writes; can land independently", "diff_url": "https://patch-diff.githubusercontent.com/raw/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/101.diff", "merged_at": "2026-05-19T04:56:02Z", "reviewer_login": "monstersebas1", "files_changed": [".omc/STATUS.md", "ecosystem.config.cjs", "scripts/doctor-scan.ts", "src/pipeline/__tests__/doctor-scan.test.ts", "src/pipeline/__tests__/doctor.test.ts", "src/pipeline/__tests__/fingerprints.test.ts", "src/pipeline/__tests__/rollup.test.ts", "src/pipeline/doctor-scan.ts", "src/pipeline/doctor.ts", "src/pipeline/fingerprints.ts", "src/pipeline/rollup.ts"], "loc_added": 1341, "loc_removed": 9, "merge_sha": "a398a2869d14ef16e84a5a2fc19e95513aa75dbf", "in_eval_set": true}
{"id": "ifleet-IF-075", "issue_number": 75, "issue_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/issues/75", "pr_number": 104, "pr_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/104", "repo": "weautomatehq1/IFleet", "title": "feat(classifier): sprint mode routing + Haiku auto-router", "body": "## Behavior\n\nWhen a sprint is submitted, before any tasks are dispatched, a lightweight Haiku call analyses the sprint goal against accumulated learnings and returns a routing decision. The decision sets the sprint mode, surfaces risk flags visible in observability, and can pause the sprint to request human clarification (deep-interview).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] A sprint in `queued` state transitions to `planning` before any tasks are assigned\n- [ ] A Haiku call is made during `planning` with the sprint goal and learnings content\n- [ ] The `RouterDecision` is stored on `SprintRecord.routerDecision` and emitted as `sprint.router_decision`\n- [ ] Any Haiku failure (timeout, malformed output, missing pool) results in safe fallback and sprint continues normally\n- [ ] When `deepInterviewRequired: true`, sprint transitions to `paused` with reason `'deep-interview required'`, IFleet posts a Discord message with the Haiku-generated questions, then polls that Discord message for a \u2705 reaction; on reaction \u2192 `Orchestrator.resumeSprint()`\n- [ ] When `deepInterviewRequired: false`, sprint transitions to `running` after router completes\n- [ ] If `.ifleet/learnings.md` is missing, router runs with empty learnings (no error)\n- [ ] Existing tests pass without wiring `workerPool` (backward-compatible optional field)\n\n## Implementation notes\n\n**Insertion point:** `SprintManager.tick()` in `src/orchestrator/sprint.ts`\n\n```typescript\nif (sprint.state.kind === 'queued') {\n  this.transition(sprintId, { kind: 'planning' });\n  const decision = await this.runAutoRouter(sprint);\n  this.applyRouterDecision(sprintId, decision);\n  return;\n}\nif (sprint.state.kind === 'planning') {\n  return; // router in flight\n}\n```\n\n**New file:** `src/orchestrator/auto-router.ts` (~60 lines) \u2014 prompt builder, Haiku call, parser, safe fallback.\n\n**Safe fallback (any error path):**\n```typescript\n{ recommendedMode: 'normal', deepInterviewRequired: false, deepInterviewQuestions: [], riskFlags: [], learningsApplied: false, raw: '' }\n```\n\n**Deep-interview resume (Q1 decision):** `onDeepInterviewRequired` callback posts via `DISCORD_IFLEET_WEBHOOK` with the Haiku-generated questions, then polls the Discord message for a qualifying reaction (`\u2705`, `+1`, `rocket`, `hooray`). On detection \u2192 `Orchestrator.resumeSprint()`. A dedicated `DiscordReactionPoller` handles the poll loop at 30-s interval with no hard timeout (waits until Seb reacts).\n\n**File-level changes:**\n\n| File | Change | ~Lines |\n|---|---|---|\n| `src/orchestrator/types.ts` | Add `RouterDecision`, extend `SprintRecord` | +20 |\n| `src/orchestrator/sprint.ts` | Options, `tick()` planning gate, `runAutoRouter()`, `applyRouterDecision()` | +80 |\n| `src/orchestrator/auto-router.ts` | **New file** | +60 |\n| `src/orchestrator/index.ts` | Wire `workerPool`, `repoRoot`, `onDeepInterviewRequired` | +15 |\n| `src/orchestrator/__tests__/sprint.test.ts` | Planning gate, fallback, deep-interview pause tests | +60 |\n\nTotal: ~235 lines net new.\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Passing risk flags as synthetic labels into `classifyTask` (Phase 5)\n- Overnight mode behavioral changes (Phase 3d)\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Soft dependency on issue #69 (learnings.md path) \u2014 if not landed, router runs with empty learnings, no error", "diff_url": "https://patch-diff.githubusercontent.com/raw/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/104.diff", "merged_at": "2026-05-19T04:58:27Z", "reviewer_login": "monstersebas1", "files_changed": ["config/routing.json", "docs/MODEL-ROUTING.md", "docs/briefs/_examples/README.md", "docs/briefs/_examples/deslop.md", "docs/briefs/_examples/ralph.md", "docs/briefs/_examples/tdd.md", "docs/briefs/_examples/ulw.md", "package.json", "src/classifier/__tests__/auto-router.test.ts", "src/classifier/__tests__/mode-routing.test.ts", "src/classifier/__tests__/modes.test.ts", "src/classifier/auto-router.ts", "src/classifier/index.ts", "src/classifier/modes.ts", "src/contracts/task.ts", "src/orchestrator/__tests__/sprint-mode.test.ts", "src/orchestrator/sprint.ts", "src/orchestrator/types.ts", "src/pipeline/types.ts"], "loc_added": 1196, "loc_removed": 7, "merge_sha": "7ad66f208e441779d309013ca4a53fe3d89586c3", "in_eval_set": true}
{"id": "ifleet-IF-072", "issue_number": 72, "issue_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/issues/72", "pr_number": 104, "pr_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/104", "repo": "weautomatehq1/IFleet", "title": "feat(classifier): sprint mode routing + Haiku auto-router", "body": "## Problem\n\nAll sprints use the same system prompt and retry policy regardless of task type. A persistence task needs different instructions than a test-driven task. There is no way to signal intent without writing it into the brief body.\n\n## Solution\n\nExtend the routing system to support sprint modes via GitHub issue labels. Four modes, each mapped to a distinct label:\n\n| Label | Mode | Behavior |\n|-------|------|----------|\n| `mode:ralph` | Persistence | Editor prompt adds: \"Do not stop until the task is fully complete. If CI fails, fix it. If the reviewer rejects, address every concern. Max 5 retry rounds.\" |\n| `mode:ulw` | Speed | Architect plans in bullet points only (no prose). Editor makes one focused change per commit. |\n| `mode:tdd` | Test-first | Architect plan must list failing tests to write FIRST, then implementation. Editor writes tests before touching implementation files. |\n| `mode:deslop` | Cleanup | Editor prompt adds: \"Remove all unnecessary complexity, dead code, unused imports. No new features. Leave the code cleaner than you found it.\" |\n\nIf no `mode:*` label is present, behavior is unchanged (default mode \u2014 current behavior).\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Label parsing\nExtend `parseLabels` (or equivalent) to extract the mode from the issue's label set and return one of: `ralph | ulw | tdd | deslop | default`.\n\n### Prompt injection\nEach mode only changes the system prompt injected into the architect and/or editor \u2014 no new pipeline stages, no new agents.\n\n### Threading\nMode must flow: `parseLabels` \u2192 routing decision \u2192 pipeline input \u2192 prompt construction. It must not be inferred from the brief body.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\nEach criterion must be independently testable:\n\n1. **Label \u2192 mode mapping** \u2014 `parseLabels` returns `ralph` for `mode:ralph`, `ulw` for `mode:ulw`, `tdd` for `mode:tdd`, `deslop` for `mode:deslop`\n2. **Distinct prompts** \u2014 each of the 4 modes produces a different effective system prompt string compared to default and to each other\n3. **Default mode** \u2014 absence of any `mode:*` label results in `default` mode with no system prompt change\n4. **Thread integrity** \u2014 the mode value is correctly passed from label parsing through to the final prompt construction step\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- Combining multiple modes on a single sprint\n- Dynamic mode switching mid-sprint\n- New pipeline stages or agents for any mode\n- A `mode:` label for the default/no-op case", "diff_url": "https://patch-diff.githubusercontent.com/raw/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/104.diff", "merged_at": "2026-05-19T04:58:27Z", "reviewer_login": "monstersebas1", "files_changed": ["config/routing.json", "docs/MODEL-ROUTING.md", "docs/briefs/_examples/README.md", "docs/briefs/_examples/deslop.md", "docs/briefs/_examples/ralph.md", "docs/briefs/_examples/tdd.md", "docs/briefs/_examples/ulw.md", "package.json", "src/classifier/__tests__/auto-router.test.ts", "src/classifier/__tests__/mode-routing.test.ts", "src/classifier/__tests__/modes.test.ts", "src/classifier/auto-router.ts", "src/classifier/index.ts", "src/classifier/modes.ts", "src/contracts/task.ts", "src/orchestrator/__tests__/sprint-mode.test.ts", "src/orchestrator/sprint.ts", "src/orchestrator/types.ts", "src/pipeline/types.ts"], "loc_added": 1196, "loc_removed": 7, "merge_sha": "7ad66f208e441779d309013ca4a53fe3d89586c3", "in_eval_set": false}
{"id": "ifleet-IF-071", "issue_number": 71, "issue_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/issues/71", "pr_number": 102, "pr_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/102", "repo": "weautomatehq1/IFleet", "title": "feat(pipeline): per-repo learnings + deep-interview phase in architect", "body": "## Problem\n\nVague briefs cause the architect to make wrong plans. When a brief says \"improve the dashboard\" or \"clean up the auth flow\", the architect guesses intent and burns a sprint on the wrong thing. There is no mechanism to ask Seb for clarification before execution begins.\n\n## Solution\n\nAdd an interview step BEFORE architect planning. When the brief is short or vague, spawn a haiku call to generate 3 clarifying questions, post them to Discord via `DISCORD_IFLEET_WEBHOOK`, and wait up to 10 minutes for a reply. If no reply arrives, proceed with planning anyway (non-blocking).\n\n## Trigger Conditions\n\nTrigger the interview if EITHER condition is true:\n- Task body is shorter than 100 characters\n- Task body contains any of these keywords: `improve`, `refactor`, `clean up`, `make better`\n\nClear briefs (> 100 chars AND no vague keywords) skip the interview entirely.\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Discord posting\n- Generate 3 clarifying questions via a haiku call with the brief as input\n- Post as a single Discord message with a numbered list (1. ... 2. ... 3. ...)\n- Use `DISCORD_IFLEET_WEBHOOK` env variable for the webhook URL\n- If `DISCORD_IFLEET_WEBHOOK` is not set, skip the interview silently and log one line\n\n### Waiting\n- Use the same polling pattern as `waitForApproval` in `src/queue/issue-commenter.ts`\n- Wait up to 10 minutes for a reply reaction or message on the Discord thread\n- After 10 minutes, log \"interview timeout \u2014 proceeding with planning\" and continue\n\n### Non-blocking guarantee\nA timeout or Discord error must never prevent the sprint from proceeding. All interview failures degrade gracefully to a skip.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\nEach criterion must be independently testable:\n\n1. **Short brief triggers interview** \u2014 a task body with fewer than 100 chars causes the interview step to run\n2. **Vague keyword triggers interview** \u2014 a task body containing \"refactor\" (or any listed keyword) causes the interview step to run\n3. **Clear brief skips interview** \u2014 a task body with > 100 chars and no vague keywords skips the interview entirely\n4. **Missing webhook skips interview** \u2014 when `DISCORD_IFLEET_WEBHOOK` is not set, the interview is skipped and a log line is emitted\n5. **Timeout does not block** \u2014 when the 10-minute window elapses with no reply, the sprint continues to architect planning\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- Parsing or interpreting the reply content\n- Multi-turn conversation (ask \u2192 answer \u2192 follow-up)\n- Changing the architect system prompt based on answers (Phase 4)\n- Any UI for managing interview responses", "diff_url": "https://patch-diff.githubusercontent.com/raw/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/102.diff", "merged_at": "2026-05-19T05:01:23Z", "reviewer_login": "monstersebas1", "files_changed": ["src/orchestrator/pipeline-bridge.ts", "src/pipeline/__tests__/architect.test.ts", "src/pipeline/__tests__/interview.test.ts", "src/pipeline/__tests__/learnings.test.ts", "src/pipeline/__tests__/runner.test.ts", "src/pipeline/architect.ts", "src/pipeline/interview.ts", "src/pipeline/learnings.ts", "src/pipeline/runner.ts", "src/pipeline/types.ts"], "loc_added": 759, "loc_removed": 3, "merge_sha": "b49ac73fb4531bf430a6fe519b2f7039d795350f", "in_eval_set": true}
{"id": "ifleet-IF-069", "issue_number": 69, "issue_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/issues/69", "pr_number": 102, "pr_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/102", "repo": "weautomatehq1/IFleet", "title": "feat(pipeline): per-repo learnings + deep-interview phase in architect", "body": "## Problem\n\nIFleet has no memory across sprints. Each sprint starts cold. Repeated mistakes are never learned \u2014 the architect makes the same wrong assumptions sprint after sprint with no way to improve.\n\n## Solution\n\nA lightweight learnings file at `<worktree>/.ifleet/learnings.md` (created if missing). The architect reads it before planning and the failure handler appends a short lesson after each sprint failure.\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Architect phase change\nBefore generating the plan, read `.ifleet/learnings.md` from the worktree root. If the file exists and is non-empty, append a section to the architect system prompt:\n\n```\n## Repo learnings\n{contents of .ifleet/learnings.md}\n```\n\nIf the file is missing or empty, no change to the prompt.\n\n### Failure handler change\nOn `task.failed` event: append a new line to `.ifleet/learnings.md` in the worktree:\n\n```\n- [ISO date] {failureReason}\n```\n\nIf the file does not exist, create it with that line as the first entry. After writing, commit and push the file from the worktree.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\nEach criterion must be independently testable:\n\n1. **Learnings injected** \u2014 when `.ifleet/learnings.md` is non-empty, the architect system prompt includes the `## Repo learnings` section with the file contents\n2. **Learnings omitted** \u2014 when `.ifleet/learnings.md` is missing or empty, the architect system prompt has no learnings section\n3. **Failure appends** \u2014 when a sprint fails, a new lesson line is appended to `.ifleet/learnings.md`\n4. **File created on first failure** \u2014 if `.ifleet/learnings.md` does not exist, the failure handler creates it with the lesson as the first line\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- RAG or vector search over learnings\n- Cross-repo sharing of learnings\n- UI for viewing or editing learnings\n- Summarizing or compressing old learnings", "diff_url": "https://patch-diff.githubusercontent.com/raw/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/102.diff", "merged_at": "2026-05-19T05:01:23Z", "reviewer_login": "monstersebas1", "files_changed": ["src/orchestrator/pipeline-bridge.ts", "src/pipeline/__tests__/architect.test.ts", "src/pipeline/__tests__/interview.test.ts", "src/pipeline/__tests__/learnings.test.ts", "src/pipeline/__tests__/runner.test.ts", "src/pipeline/architect.ts", "src/pipeline/interview.ts", "src/pipeline/learnings.ts", "src/pipeline/runner.ts", "src/pipeline/types.ts"], "loc_added": 759, "loc_removed": 3, "merge_sha": "b49ac73fb4531bf430a6fe519b2f7039d795350f", "in_eval_set": false}
{"id": "ifleet-IF-044", "issue_number": 44, "issue_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/issues/44", "pr_number": 47, "pr_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/47", "repo": "weautomatehq1/IFleet", "title": "feat(classifier): reviewer >= architect invariant + complexity:low rule-cap test", "body": "## Symptom\nFor tasks where the scorer would have chosen a low tier (e.g. haiku) but a routing rule promotes the architect, the reviewer slot keeps mirroring the scorer-derived tier instead of tracking the architect's final model. The reviewer can therefore end up weaker than the architect on the same task.\n\n## Why it matters\nThe reviewer's job is a second opinion at architect strength. A weaker reviewer can rubber-stamp work that a stronger architect produced, which defeats the cross-check the pipeline relies on.\n\n## Reproduction\n1. Open an issue with a title that matches one of the architect routing rules (e.g. text mentioning \"design\", \"security review\", or \"migration\")\n2. Do not add `complexity:high`, `priority:high`, or any other tier-bumping label\n3. Run the classifier on this task\n4. Observe the architect resolves to Sonnet (rule promoted, then the opus cap applied) while the reviewer resolves to Haiku\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- The reviewer's model is always at the same tier or higher than the architect's model in the same classification result\n- This invariant holds across every path:\n  - scorer-only (no rule match, no complexity label)\n  - rule-override (architect role rule matches, with and without complexity labels)\n  - explicit `complexity:high`\n  - explicit `complexity:low`\n- A unit test enforces the invariant for each of those four paths\n\n## Out of scope\n- Changing tier definitions\n- Introducing new label types\n- Touching the architect opus cap from PR #41\n\n## History\nThe behavior pre-dates PR #41 but PR #41's opus cap makes the gap easier to surface, so the cleanup belongs in the same family of work. Flagged by the independent reviewer of PR #41.\n\n**AFK** \u2014 agent can execute autonomously.", "diff_url": "https://patch-diff.githubusercontent.com/raw/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/47.diff", "merged_at": "2026-05-13T23:17:01Z", "reviewer_login": "monstersebas1", "files_changed": ["src/classifier/__tests__/classifier.test.ts", "src/classifier/index.ts"], "loc_added": 155, "loc_removed": 3, "merge_sha": "e8f64b2e5d8da3644d33a08cd802ca1151b5315e", "in_eval_set": true}
{"id": "ifleet-IF-043", "issue_number": 43, "issue_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/issues/43", "pr_number": 47, "pr_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/47", "repo": "weautomatehq1/IFleet", "title": "feat(classifier): reviewer >= architect invariant + complexity:low rule-cap test", "body": "## Context\nPR #41 introduced the policy that the architect role runs on Sonnet by default and is only promoted to Opus when the issue carries a `complexity:high` label. `complexity:low` is also supposed to force Sonnet even when something else (scorer or routing rule) would otherwise push to Opus.\n\nThe PR ships an explicit test for `complexity:low` defeating a **scorer-driven** opus promotion. It does not test the same outcome for a **rule-driven** opus promotion (the routing rules that hardcode opus for architect, like the SQL/migrations rule). The behavior is correct by code trace but not exercised by the test suite.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- A new unit test exists that:\n  - Submits a task whose title or body matches a routing rule that maps `architect \u2192 claude-opus-4-7`\n  - Includes `complexity:low` in the labels\n  - Asserts the resulting architect model resolves to `claude-sonnet-4-6`\n- A second unit test asserts the same outcome when no complexity label is present at all (the default cap), distinct from the `complexity:low` case\n- All existing tests still pass\n\n## Out of scope\n- Changing the routing rule shape or schema\n- Refactoring the classifier\n- Adding new label types\n\n## Notes\nIndependent reviewer of PR #41 flagged this as the single test gap worth a follow-up. Not a blocker for the merge.\n\n**AFK** \u2014 agent can execute autonomously.", "diff_url": "https://patch-diff.githubusercontent.com/raw/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/47.diff", "merged_at": "2026-05-13T23:17:01Z", "reviewer_login": "monstersebas1", "files_changed": ["src/classifier/__tests__/classifier.test.ts", "src/classifier/index.ts"], "loc_added": 155, "loc_removed": 3, "merge_sha": "e8f64b2e5d8da3644d33a08cd802ca1151b5315e", "in_eval_set": false}
{"id": "ifleet-IF-029", "issue_number": 29, "issue_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/issues/29", "pr_number": 31, "pr_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/31", "repo": "weautomatehq1/IFleet", "title": "feat(orchestrator): include durationMs in sprint.completed event payload", "body": "When SprintManager emits `sprint.completed`, the payload has `from`/`to` but no timing info. Add `durationMs` so observability consumers can report sprint duration without correlating separate events.\n\n## Spec \u2014 exactly what to change\n\n**File: `src/orchestrator/sprint.ts`**\n\nIn the `transition()` method, the current `sprint.completed` branch emits:\n```typescript\n{ from: current.state.kind, to: next.kind }\n```\n\nChange it so that when `next.kind === 'completed'`, it computes duration and adds it:\n```typescript\nconst durationMs =\n  current.state.kind === 'running' ? now - current.state.startedAt : 0;\n// then include in payload for completed transition only:\n{ from: current.state.kind, to: next.kind, durationMs, prs: next.prs }\n```\n\nThe `now` variable is already declared at the top of `transition()`. `current.state` is `SprintState`. `SprintState` with `kind: 'running'` has `startedAt: number` \u2014 use a type-narrowed check.\n\n**File: `src/orchestrator/__tests__/sprint.test.ts`**\n\nAdd one test after the existing `transition` tests. Use `makeManager` from `./helpers`. Pattern:\n```typescript\ntest('transition: sprint.completed payload includes durationMs', () => {\n  const h = makeManager({ now: () => 1000 });\n  try {\n    const rec = h.manager.startSprint({ mode: 'normal', goal: 't' });\n    h.manager.transition(rec.id, { kind: 'running', startedAt: 1000 });\n    // advance time\n    h.env.now = () => 3000;  // if makeManager supports now override \u2014 check helpers.ts\n    const events = h.env.events;\n    h.manager.transition(rec.id, { kind: 'completed', at: 3000, prs: [] });\n    const completedEvt = events.find(e => e.kind === 'sprint.completed');\n    assert.equal(typeof completedEvt?.payload.durationMs, 'number');\n  } finally {\n    h.env.cleanup();\n  }\n});\n```\nCheck `helpers.ts` to see how `now` is overridden, and adapt accordingly.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- `npm test` passes (all existing tests + new test green)\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` passes  \n- Only `src/orchestrator/sprint.ts` and `src/orchestrator/__tests__/sprint.test.ts` modified\n- No changes to `OrchestratorEvent` interface in types.ts \u2014 payload is `Record<string, unknown>` so extra fields are fine\n\n## Out of scope\n- Do NOT add durationMs to SprintRecord itself\n- Do NOT touch any other event types\n- Do NOT modify types.ts", "diff_url": "https://patch-diff.githubusercontent.com/raw/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/31.diff", "merged_at": "2026-05-13T18:56:47Z", "reviewer_login": "monstersebas1", "files_changed": ["src/orchestrator/__tests__/sprint.test.ts", "src/orchestrator/sprint.ts"], "loc_added": 27, "loc_removed": 1, "merge_sha": "aa1008b25a01a4fc44d8df6debcdbe760d9a007d", "in_eval_set": true}
{"id": "ifleet-IF-020", "issue_number": 20, "issue_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/issues/20", "pr_number": 24, "pr_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/24", "repo": "weautomatehq1/IFleet", "title": "feat(classifier): build brief \u2192 routing decision module", "body": "## Context\n\n\\`config/routing.json\\` defines keyword and file-glob rules for picking provider/model per task. Nothing reads it yet \u2014 routing is hardcoded in \\`scripts/run-smoke.ts\\`.\n\n## Goal\n\nBuild \\`src/classifier/index.ts\\` that exports:\n\n\\`\\`\\`ts\nexport function classifyTask(task: { title: string; body: string; labels: string[] }): RoutingDecision\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n- Load \\`config/routing.json\\` at startup\n- Match task title + body against \\`rules[].match.keywords\\` (case-insensitive substring)\n- Fall through to \\`pipeline\\` defaults when no rule matches\n- Return a \\`RoutingDecision\\` shaped like the existing type in \\`src/pipeline/types.ts\\`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- \\`classifyTask\\` returns correct provider/model for keyword matches\n- Falls back to \\`pipeline.architect\\` / \\`pipeline.editor\\` defaults when no rule matches\n- Unit tests cover: keyword hit, no match (default), multi-rule priority (first match wins)\n- Typecheck + lint + test pass", "diff_url": "https://patch-diff.githubusercontent.com/raw/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/24.diff", "merged_at": "2026-05-13T17:36:31Z", "reviewer_login": "monstersebas1", "files_changed": ["src/classifier/__tests__/classifier.test.ts", "src/classifier/index.ts"], "loc_added": 169, "loc_removed": 0, "merge_sha": "56ba3a0d10fe55a3a72dc7262fd2522a1abbc9e7", "in_eval_set": true}
{"id": "ifleet-IF-016", "issue_number": 16, "issue_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/issues/16", "pr_number": 18, "pr_url": "https://github.com/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/18", "repo": "weautomatehq1/IFleet", "title": "fix(scripts): derive branch name from issue title in run-smoke.ts", "body": "## Problem\n\nThe branch name in `run-smoke.ts` is hardcoded:\n```ts\nconst branchName = `chore/smoke-${rawTask.issueNumber}-remove-stale-todo`;\n```\n\nThis only works for issue #6. Any new issue will get a branch named after the stale TODO task.\n\n## Solution\n\nDerive the branch name from `rawTask.title` at runtime:\n- Lowercase the title\n- Replace spaces and special chars with `-`\n- Truncate to ~50 chars\n- Prefix with `chore/smoke-<issueNumber>-`\n\nExample: issue #7 \"feat: add classifier module\" \u2192 `feat/smoke-7-add-classifier-module`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Branch name reflects the picked issue's title\n- No hardcoded string references\n- Typecheck + lint + test pass", "diff_url": "https://patch-diff.githubusercontent.com/raw/weautomatehq1/IFleet/pull/18.diff", "merged_at": "2026-05-13T16:34:26Z", "reviewer_login": "monstersebas1", "files_changed": ["scripts/run-smoke.ts", "src/utils/__tests__/branch-name.test.ts", "src/utils/branch-name.ts", "vitest.config.ts"], "loc_added": 105, "loc_removed": 2, "merge_sha": "7bd6c17a089cd1ec5bbc3afe2dc2012b1d9450e9", "in_eval_set": true}
